BTU  (Mobility Units)
  How movement costs are calculated.

DESCRIPTION
  Every sector, ship, and land unit has a mobility value.  Movement
  consumes mobility.  Mobility regenerates each update.

  SECTORS
  Sector mobility is used when civilians or goods pass through.
  Moving through a highway (+) sector costs roughly half as much.
  Sectors start each update with a fresh mobility budget.

  SHIPS
  Ships gain mobility each update based on their speed rating.
  Moving one sector costs approximately 5/speed mobility points.
  A ship with 0 mobility cannot navigate.

  LAND UNITS
  Land units gain mobility each update.
  Moving one sector costs 1 mobility point for infantry.
  Faster units cost less per sector.

  CIVILIANS AND EXPLORE
  Civilians use sector mobility when exploring or moving.
  Each step along a path costs roughly 1 mobility per civ moved
  (less through highways).

  REGENERATION
  Mobility regenerates to the cap during each update.
  The cap is determined by the unit type and tech level.
  Sectors regenerate to 127 each update (standard config).

